TITLE: Suspect in Illinois killings and passenger dead after fiery crash following police chase in Oklahoma, authorities say
SUMMARY: A woman and a suspect in the killings of four members of the same family in Romeoville, Illinois, died after a police chase and vehicle crash, the Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation said.

TITLE: Hollywood chiefs and writers to resume negotiations Thursday after attendees 'encouraged' by talks
SUMMARY: Writers and heads of the four major studios are set to meet for a second consecutive day Thursday as they try to hammer out a deal that puts to an end the historic strike that has frozen Hollywood.

TITLE: Bank of England pauses rate hikes as inflation falls
SUMMARY: The Bank of England paused its historic interest rate hiking campaign for the first time in nearly two years Thursday after inflation fell unexpectedly in August.

TITLE: What could happen if the government shuts down
SUMMARY: The prospect of a US government shutdown grows more likely with each passing day as lawmakers have yet to reach a deal to extend funding past a critical deadline at the end of the month.

TITLE: India suspends visas for Canadian nationals as diplomatic spat deepens
SUMMARY: India has suspended visa services for Canadian citizens, escalating a diplomatic spat between both countries after Ottawa accused New Delhi of potentially being behind the assassination of a Sikh separatist activist on its soil.

TITLE: Russia's war in Ukraine
SUMMARY: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky is expected to meet with US President Joe Biden on Thursday and visit the US Capitol as he appeals for more support for Kyiv. Follow here for live updates.

TITLE: Azerbaijan says it has retaken breakaway Armenian enclave after separatists surrender
SUMMARY: Azerbaijan said it had taken back the breakaway region of Nagorno-Karabakh after launching a lightning 24-hour assault that forced ethnic Armenian forces to surrender and agree to a Russia-brokered ceasefire.

TITLE: Zelensky faces a more splintered GOP as he returns to Capitol Hill looking for aid
SUMMARY: Ukraine President Volodymyr Zelenksy will return to Capitol Hill Thursday for his second visit since his country was besieged by Russia. Only this time, the political landscape has shifted.

TITLE: China just stopped exporting two minerals the world's chipmakers need
SUMMARY: China's exports of two rare minerals essential for manufacturing semiconductors fell to zero in August, a month after Beijing imposed curbs on sales overseas, citing national security.

TITLE: Live sports is migrating to streaming, taking with it a superpower of the cable TV bundle
SUMMARY: The cable bundle is losing its biggest edge over the streaming competition: live sports.

TITLE: Vivek Ramaswamy made a splash on last month's debate stage. But does he have staying power?
SUMMARY: After a splashy debut at last month's first Republican presidential debate, Vivek Ramaswamy has gone from an unknown to a contender who's now facing questions about his youth and lack of political experience, especially given his position as the first millennial to run for the Republican presidential nomination. He's being vetted over how he made his millions at the biotech company he started in his late 20s and frequent shifts in his foreign policy platform. He's also facing questions about how he would, if elected, enact his agenda and defend it from legal challenges.

TITLE: Calculate your monthly student loan bill under Biden's SAVE plan
SUMMARY: A new federal student loan repayment plan known as SAVE (Saving on a Valuable Education) could lower monthly payments for millions of borrowers. Use CNN's calculator to see how much your monthly payment would be this year if you're enrolled in SAVE.

TITLE: 'Godfather' of illicit wildlife trade jailed in US for trafficking rhino horns worth $2 million
SUMMARY: A US court on Tuesday sentenced a wildlife trade kingpin to 18 months in prison for conspiring to traffic hundreds of kilos of rhino horns, in a ruling conservation groups said would cause a major blow to the illicit business.

TITLE: Trump is not invincible in Republican race -- but still lacks a single strong challenger
SUMMARY: All hope is not dead for Donald Trump's Republican rivals, but anyone seeking to emerge as a genuine challenger must soon begin to coalesce opposition to the ex-president to slow his chase toward a third straight GOP nomination.

TITLE: Memorial from broken headstones to mark desecrated Jewish cemetery in Belarus
SUMMARY: When a large Jewish cemetery was paved over last century to create a sports ground in Belarus, the headstones were used to make roads and buildings. Recovered remnants are now being used to create a memorial on the site.

TITLE: A manhunt is underway for a homicide suspect who was accidentally released from an Indianapolis detention center, officials say
SUMMARY: A manhunt is underway for a suspect in a 2021 killing who was accidentally released from a detention center in Indianapolis last week, a sheriff's office said Tuesday, asking for the public's help finding him.

TITLE: World must learn from Bosnian war in dealing with sexual violence in Ukraine conflict, report says
SUMMARY: The world must learn from the mistakes made after the war in Bosnia to avoid putting Ukrainian victims of rape and conflict-related sexual violence through decades of trauma, a new expert report has warned.

TITLE: Sunak delays crucial UK climate targets, with one eye on the next election
SUMMARY: Britain will delay a series of key climate targets, its beleaguered Prime Minister Rishi Sunak said Wednesday at a hastily organized press conference, in a move that angered businesses and political allies and intensified the government's assault on green policies.

TITLE: Toshiba is set to delist in Japan after 74 years as part of $14 billion deal
SUMMARY: Toshiba said on Thursday that a $14 billion tender offer from private equity firm Japan Industrial Partners (JIP) had ended in success â€” a deal which paves the way for the embattled industrial conglomerate to go private.

TITLE: A grad student 'full of dreams and hopes' was fatally struck by a police car. What an officer said about her later has sparked outrage from Seattle to Capitol Hill
SUMMARY: An effervescent young woman with a bubbly laugh and a radiant smile. A stellar student on the cusp of earning her master's degree. A beloved daughter making her mark thousands of miles from home.

TITLE: Powerball jackpot grows to $725 million after no winning ticket Wednesday
SUMMARY: Powerball players now have the chance to win an estimated $725 million jackpot this weekend after Wednesday night's drawing produced no big winner.

TITLE: House Democrats weigh risky strategy: Whether to save McCarthy
SUMMARY: House Democrats have begun internal discussions about how to deal with the prospects of a chaotic situation: The possibility that Speaker Kevin McCarthy could lose his job in an unprecedented vote on the floor.

TITLE: 2 police officers being investigated after telling a father his 11-year-old daughter could face child porn charges for sending images to a man online
SUMMARY: The police chief in Columbus, Ohio, is condemning an incident in which two officers told a father his 11-year-old daughter could face child porn charges for sending images to a man online.

TITLE: Huawei wants to go all in on AI for the next decade
SUMMARY: Huawei has joined the list of companies that want to be all about artificial intelligence.

TITLE: Indonesia jails woman who recited Muslim prayer before trying pork on TikTok
SUMMARY: A Muslim woman has been sentenced to two years in prison under Indonesia's blasphemy law over a video she shared on TikTok which showed her reciting an Islamic prayer before trying out pork while visiting the tourist island of Bali.

TITLE: Ukraine's counteroffensive may be painful. But its success is crucial to wider European security
SUMMARY: In the basements of Orikhiv, Ukrainian troops stand by the walls. Even though they are underground, the huge Russian bombs that routinely land could collapse everything above onto them, and so the edges of their underground world are safer.

TITLE: Why has Doja Cat's new song 'Balut' landed her in hot water with some Filipino listeners?
SUMMARY: American rapper Doja Cat has landed in hot water with listeners in the Philippines after naming her latest single after a Filipino street food.

TITLE: McCarthy plots new push to avoid shutdown but faces renewed resistance in ranks
SUMMARY: Speaker Kevin McCarthy, facing growing unrest in the GOP conference, is moving on a new plan to keep the government open for another month -- but he is again encountering resistance from conservative hardliners who are threatening to derail the effort and oust him from his powerful perch atop the House.

TITLE: Poland will stop providing weapons to Ukraine as dispute over grain imports deepens
SUMMARY: Poland said Wednesday it will stop providing weapons to Ukraine amid a growing dispute between the two countries over a temporary ban on Ukrainian grain imports.

TITLE: Trump ramps up attention on Iowa even as he keeps one eye on the general election
SUMMARY: Donald Trump is shifting gears as the Iowa caucuses draw closer, taking a more active approach to campaigning in the Hawkeye State in order to quash any possibility that one of his primary rivals could catch up to him there.
